\title{Compute E-value for unmeasured confounding}
\description{
Compute the E-value for unmeasured confounding (VanderWeele and Ding, 2017).

The E-value quantifies the minimum strength of confounding association
needed to fully explain away an observed treatment effect.
For a risk ratio less than 1, use its reciprocal before applying the formula.
}
\usage{
